    <abstract audience="internal" id="aspace_d6fea47220cdd8a6b878c721296d720d">Research files, correspondence, typed and handwritten research notes, surveys, articles, reviews and drafts, research-related, aerial photographs, spot maps, and audio cassettes of the Cornell Ph.D. alumnus in Conservation Biology, Natural Resource Policy and Planning (1986) and later Senior Research Associate and Program Director of the Cornell University Laboratory of Ornithology (1981-1989), Thomas S. Litwin, document his research at the Laboratory and the Sapsucker Woods dating from 1938-1990 (bulk dates 1978-1990).</abstract>
